# See time from other timezones with a Terminal command

# awoo~
TZ=Australia/NSW date

# meow~
TZ=Europe/London date

# Set TZ and call date; check /usr/share/zoneinfo. but this is mostly timezones and not locations
# If the zone doesn't exist, some implementations of date will put it in the output and use UTC or local time behind your back. (rude implementations!)

# (thanks lily whoops [@ilylily@witches.live] for all this!)

# you can use this wherever, in your terminal's rc (.bashrc), even
